        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 6 at 9:26PM MDT until July 6 at 9:45PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 925 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles south of
Kanorado, moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...70 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar Indicated. This storm has a history of 60-70 mph
winds.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect considerable
tree damage. Wind damage is also likely to mobile homes,
roofs, and outbuildings.

Locations impacted include...
Burlington.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 70 in Colorado between mile markers 429 and 450.
Highway 385 between mile markers 170 and 195.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
